						<summary>

						<p>Slab (No. 3) built into the sluice in a field called ‘Kambaḷa-gadde’.</p>						

						<p>Mallikārjuna, 1458 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 13 • •, Bahudhānya, Vaiśākha śu.,</hi> all other details being lost. The cyclic year corresponds to 1458 A.D.; the <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> in Vaiśākha falls sometime in April-May.</p>						

						<p>It seems to grant a money a income by the king at the instance of <hi rend="italic">mahāpradhāna</hi> Siddappa-daṇṇāyaka. The details are lost. The record was written by <hi rend="italic">karaṇika</hi> Liṅgarasa.</p>						

						</summary>
